Only found this through the Lord of Spirits podcast but 4 Maccabees has to be the most obscure book of the Bible I have heard of. Starts as a philosophical discourse on the sovereignty of pure reason and continues with brutal graphic descriptions of the torture of Jewish martyrs.

It's like a Leibniz essay exalting objective rational thought mixed with heavy torture scenes from Gene Wolfe's BotNS. Not even Deuterocanonical, but like in an appendix to the Slavonic canon. Pretty sure even the Catholic bros don't have this one, not to even speak of Prot bros.
That's not to say only us Orthodox are allowed to read it ofc. or that it's illicit for others, I invite everyone to check it out.

Conceptually perfect text. Refusal to submit to the worship of idols under pain of being broken on a wheel and burned alive taken as an absolute triumph of rationality and objective reason over sensuality, emotions, subjectivity, etc. Could have been written in the 17th century.
Its original title apparently literally is "On the Sovereignty of Reason".
